        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 2:27PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 227 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Douglas, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Breckenridge...                   Douglas...
Garber...                         Bison...
Fairmont...                       Hayward...
Covington...                      Enid...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
northern Oklahoma.</instruction>
